    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Order containing around 211 species in ten families including hornbills, bee-eaters, rollers, hoopoes, todies, and motmots. They are a heterogeneous group of hole-nesting birds, many with long pointed bills and blue or green in plumage, and all having two toes joined at base.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
